                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Ashkenazi (French?) semi-cursive script of 16th century. Mosheh Merḳis: inscirbed with his name in the colophon, folios 23v, 27r. The name 'Mosheh' has been marked with pen designs, e.g. folio 15r.  Ashkenazi (French?) semi-cursive script of 13th century. Yosef ben Natan: inscribed with his name, together with the name of Shimshon ben Yehudah, in the colophon, 1257, folio 209r. Ashkenazi semi-cursive of 13th century. Ashkenazi (French) square of c15th century.</scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
